        <h1>Connect to Mexico VPN & Proceed</h1><div class="important-note">
        <strong>Important Note:</strong> This page will guide you through connecting to a VPN. We cannot automatically establish a VPN connection for you. Please follow the steps carefully.
    </div>

    <h2>Step 1: Understand VPNs</h2>
    <p>A Virtual Private Network (VPN) creates a secure, encrypted connection over a less secure network, such as the internet. It allows you to appear as if you are browsing from a different location, which is what we need to connect to Mexico.</p>

    <h2>Step 2: Choose and Install a Free VPN App (No Login Required)</h2>
    <p>Here are some popular free VPN services that often offer servers in Mexico and typically don't require an extensive login process. <strong>Please research and choose one that you feel comfortable with.</strong> Click the links below to visit their official download pages:</p>
    <ol>
        <li>
            <strong>Proton VPN Free:</strong>
            <ul>
                <li><a href="https://protonvpn.com/download" target="_blank">Download Proton VPN</a></li>
                <li>Install the app and look for a free server location in Mexico.</li>
            </ul>
        </li>
        <li>
            <strong>TunnelBear (Limited Free Data):</strong>
            <ul>
                <li><a href="https://www.tunnelbear.com/download" target="_blank">Download TunnelBear</a></li>
                <li>Connect to a Mexican server.</li>
            </ul>
        </li>
        <li>
            <strong>Windscribe (Limited Free Data):</strong>
            <ul>
                <li><a href="https://windscribe.com/download" target="_blank">Download Windscribe</a></li>
                <li>Select a Mexican server and connect.</li>
            </ul>
        </li>
        <li>
            <strong>Other Options:</strong> Search your app store for "free VPN Mexico no login" but be cautious and check reviews.
        </li>
    </ol>

    <p><strong>Remember:</strong> "Free" VPNs often come with limitations. Always download from official sources to ensure security.</p>

    <h2>Step 3: Connect to a Mexican VPN Server</h2>
    <ol>
        <li>Open the VPN app you just installed.</li>
        <li>Look for an option to select a server location.</li>
        <li>Choose a server located in <strong>Mexico</strong>.</li>
        <li>Click the "Connect" button within the VPN app.</li>
        <li>Wait for confirmation. You may also see a VPN icon on your device.</li>
    </ol>

    <h2>Step 4: Confirm & Proceed</h2>
    <p>Once you are sure you're connected to a Mexican server, click the button below to verify and continue.</p>

    <div class="button-container">
        <button id="proceedButton">I'm Connected to Mexico VPN! Proceed</button>
        <button id="retryButton" style="margin-top: 10px; display: none;">Check Again</button>
        <p id="statusMessage" style="margin-top:10px;"></p>
        <p id="ipDetails" style="font-size: 0.9em; color: #555;"></p>
